FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (FRD) 
Project Title: Project Pokedex (subject to change) 
1. Introduction 
This document describes the functional requirements of the system. 
It defines what the system shall do and the features it will provide to users 
2. System Overview 
The system is a web application developed to: 
● Handle real-time image recognition using YOLOv8 and CLIP. 
● Secure user authentication and personalized collection storage. 
● Allow Users to browse, organize, and manage their collections. 
● Display card metadata retrieved from external APIs. 
● Have voice-assisted interaction for accessibility and engagement.  
3. Functional Requirements 
The functional requirements are listed below in “The system shall…” format. 
FR-1 
The system shall allow users to scan and identify cards in their collection. 
FR-2 
The system shall display relevant card data to the user such as trade and meta information. 
FR-3 
The system shall allow users to create profiles for account management. 
FR-3 
The system shall store data related to card information, user emails, and authentication keys in 
the database. 
FR-4 
The system shall allow users to interact with AI agent to further assist with card information 
acquisition. 
FR-5 
The system shall allow users to delete their scan, user, and app data. 
FR-6 
The system shall use generative AI for improving accessibility to users with voice assistance and 
generative text. 
